The paper focuses on automatic comment generation for code snippets, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach involves utilizing domain features of code snippets, such as symbols and identifiers, to generate comments, which suggests a natural language processing (NLP) component (cs.CL). The paper also mentions making ablation studies to determine the effects of different parts in the proposed module, which suggests a machine learning (ML) component (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to build a large dataset from open projects in GitHub. Finally, the paper proposes a new attention module that improves the performance of existing approaches, which suggests an artificial intelligence (AI) component (cs.AI).
